  "history": {
    "en": "Ancient herding breed from the Chodsko region of Bohemia, also known as Chodský pes, dating back to the 14th century. Bred as herding and guard dogs by the Chodové people, nearly extinct after WWII but revived in the 1980s. Received provisional FCI recognition in 2019 and is part of the AKC Foundation Stock Service.",
    "zh": "来自波希米亚霍茨科地区的古老牧羊犬种，又称霍茨基犬，可追溯至14世纪。由霍德人培育为牧羊犬和护卫犬，二战后几乎灭绝，但在20世纪80年代复兴。2019年获得FCI临时认可，并列入AKC基础品种服务计划。"
  },
